            <thetext>The IE9 Pre (9.0.7916.6000) throws in IE9 Standard Mode the INVALID_CHARACTER_ERR when document.createElement is used with a markup. It seems that the IE9 Standard Mode is now compatible to the DOM specification.

So a element creation with a Sting as markup like:
document.createElement(&quot;&lt;INPUT TYPE=&#39;RADIO&#39; NAME=&#39;RADIOTEST&#39; VALUE=&#39;Second Choice&#39;&gt;&quot;);

Is not possible anymore with IE9 in Standard Mode.</thetext>
